ected area of popular literature is presented here for the first time. The author reconstructs the journalistic and internal debates about its origins and explores the changing poetics of this genre through a series of close readings.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 4aKommunistische Pinkertons. 4aRussische Literatur des 20. Jahrhunderts. 4aWissenschaftliche Fantastik. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK GESAMTPAKET / COMPLETE PACKAGE 2013z9783110317350oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PAKET LITERATURWISSENSCHAFT  2013z9783110317251oZDB-23-DLW08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Complete Package 2014z9783110369526oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literature 2014z9783110370331oZDB-23-DLW40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783412211899423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9783412211899.jpg  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGGb2013  aZDB-23-DGGb2014  aZDB-23-DLWb2013  aZDB-23-DLWb2014